subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnostic characters.
Antenna reaching base of wing if bent backward (
Fig. 33
). Prescutum and presutural scutum with one relatively broad grey stripe at middle (
Fig. 34
). Wing whitish subhyaline; costal and subcostal cells brownish (
Fig. 35
). Tergite 9 with posterior margin of tergal saucer broadly emarginated; anterior part narrowed, elevated into a quadrate-shaped sclerotized plate (
Fig. 37
). Gonocoxite point-apexed with raised distal part (
Figs 36, 38, 39
). Clasper of gonostylus blade-shaped; beak sclerotized and spike-shaped (
Fig. 39
).
